    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Current status of it: \r\nWe talked to Iuri, and I also looked at how Embark is organised now. Agreed that the previous implementation contained everything we need, but the basic set of features can be minimal and the list created by you already includes everything we need at the beginning.\r\nAnd we don't even need to invent something here — the previous solution was good enough. The only problem is that it doesn't work anymore, all features for debugging were removed from `status-react`, and we need to carefully re-implement them.\r\n\r\nMore importantly, if we decide to continue with a web server, we don't even need a cli. The idea is the following — we can simply run a web server and accept some specific requests. Which means that instead of using some third-party tools we can easily use POST and GET requests.\r\n\r\nThe only tricky part is discovery, it's probably not that important, but I am going to check it as well.",
